BUG-001 (Severity: Medium) — Mobile swipe-down to duck is broken

Requirement: REQUIREMENT.md §2.1 — "Swiping down on the screen causes the dinosaur to duck (mobile)"

Root cause:
- `touchstart` always fires `handleAction()` → `dino.jump()`, setting `jumping = true`
- When finger moves down ≥30px, `touchmove` calls `dino.duck(true)`
- `duck()` guards with `if (on && !this.jumping)` — since `jumping` is now `true`, duck is silently ignored
- Duck via swipe is therefore NEVER activated; the dino jumps instead

Affected code:
- index.html:239 — touchstart fires handleAction() → jump
- index.html:248 — touchmove fires dino.duck(true)
- index.html:132 — duck() guard blocks duck while jumping

Suggested fix:
Defer the jump action from touchstart to touchend, firing jump only when total touch displacement is small (a tap, not a swipe). On touchend: if |dy| < ~20px → jump; otherwise, the swipe was already handled as a duck.

